  array('id' => '65','post_id' => '26','key' => 'description','value' => '<p>Thank you for choosing <strong>WhatsML</strong>. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and protect your information when you use our SaaS platform and services related to WhatsApp automation and marketing.</p><p>By accessing or using our service, you agree to the terms of this Privacy Policy.</p><hr><h3>1.1 Personal Information</h3><p>We may collect the following personal information when you register or use our platform:</p><ul><li><p>Full Name</p></li><li><p>Email Address</p></li><li><p>Phone Number (including WhatsApp numbers)</p></li><li><p>Company or Business Information</p></li><li><p>Billing &amp; Payment Details</p></li></ul><h3>1.2 Account &amp; Usage Information</h3><ul><li><p>Login credentials (hashed and encrypted)</p></li><li><p>IP address, device, and browser type</p></li><li><p>Chat interactions, automation workflows, and campaign settings</p></li><li><p>Access logs and activity logs</p></li></ul><h3>1.3 Data from Integrations</h3><p>When you connect third-party services like WhatsApp Cloud API or Web API, we may collect:</p><ul><li><p>WhatsApp number and business profile info</p></li><li><p>Chat message metadata</p></li><li><p>Contacts and conversation history (if permitted by you)</p></li></ul><hr><h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2><p>We use the collected information to:</p><ul><li><p>Provide and maintain our platform and services</p></li><li><p>Authenticate users and secure accounts</p></li><li><p>Manage customer support and troubleshooting</p></li><li><p>Analyze platform usage to improve features</p></li><li><p>Send system updates, billing notices, and alerts</p></li><li><p>Customize AI chat responses and automation settings</p></li><li><p>Ensure compliance with legal and regulatory requirements</p></li></ul><hr><h2>3. Data Sharing &amp; Disclosure</h2><p>We <strong>do not sell</strong> or rent your personal data. We may share information only:</p><ul><li><p>With trusted third-party service providers (e.g., payment processors, cloud hosting)</p></li><li><p>With law enforcement if required by applicable laws or legal processes</p></li><li><p>If necessary to protect the rights and safety of our users or our company</p></li><li><p>In case of a business transfer (e.g., merger, acquisition)</p></li></ul><hr><h2>4. Data Security</h2><p>We implement a variety of security measures including:</p><ul><li><p>End-to-end encryption for sensitive data</p></li><li><p>Role-based access control</p></li><li><p>Secure API integrations with token authentication</p></li><li><p>Regular security audits and vulnerability assessments</p></li></ul><hr><h2>5. Your Rights and Choices</h2><p>You have the right to:</p><ul><li><p>Access, update, or delete your personal information</p></li><li><p>Request a copy of the data we hold about you</p></li><li><p>Withdraw your consent or opt-out of communications</p></li><li><p>Close your account at any time from your dashboard</p></li></ul><p>For any requests, contact us at: <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" href="mailto:privacy@amcoders.com"><strong>privacy@amcoders.com</strong></a></p><hr><h2>6. Cookies &amp; Tracking Technologies</h2><p>We use cookies and similar technologies to enhance your experience, remember preferences, and analyze platform performance. You can manage cookie preferences through your browser settings.</p><hr><h2>7. Third-Party Links</h2><p>Our platform may contain links to third-party websites or tools. We are not responsible for the privacy practices of these external platforms. Please review their privacy policies before interacting.</p><hr><h2>8. Children’s Privacy</h2><p>WhatsML is not intended for individuals under the age of 18. We do not knowingly collect data from children. If we become aware, we will take steps to delete such data.</p><hr><h2>9. Changes to This Policy</h2><p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. If we make material changes, we will notify you via email or through our platform. Continued use of our service constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.</p><hr><h2>10. Contact Us</h2><p>If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact:</p><p><strong>amcoders</strong><br>Email: <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" href="mailto:privacy@amcoders.com">privacy@amcoders.com</a></p>'),
  array('id' => '66','post_id' => '26','key' => 'seo','value' => '{"title":"terms and conditions","description":"Thank you for choosing WhatsML. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and protect your information when you use our SaaS platform and services related to WhatsApp automation and marketing.","tags":"wa, whatsapp, devstation, qserve, whatsserve"}'),
  array('id' => '67','post_id' => '27','key' => 'description','value' => '<p>Welcome to <b>WhatsML</b>, an AI-based whatsapp marketing & automation platform. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and protect your information when you use our SaaS platform and services related to WhatsApp automation and marketing.</p><p><strong>#Information We Collect</strong></p><p><strong>Personal Information:</strong> When you create an account or use our services, we may collect information such as your name, email address, and payment details.</p><p><strong>Usage Data:</strong> We collect data on how you use our website, including interactions, clicks, and time spent on different pages.</p><p><strong>Cookies:</strong> We use cookies to enhance your experience, remember your preferences, and understand how you interact with our services.</p><p><strong>#How We Use Your Information</strong></p><p><strong>Service Delivery:</strong> We use your information to provide and improve our social media management services.</p><p><strong>Communication:</strong> We may send you emails or notifications about updates, new features, or other relevant information.</p><p><strong>Analytics:</strong> We analyze your usage data to improve our website and tailor content to your preferences.</p><p><strong>#Sharing Your Information</strong></p><p><strong>Third-Party Services:</strong> We may share your information with third-party service providers to help us deliver our services (e.g., payment processors).</p><p><strong>Legal Compliance:</strong> We may disclose your information if required by law or in response to a legal request.</p><p><strong>Data Security</strong> We take reasonable measures to protect your personal information from unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, or destruction. However, no internet transmission is completely secure.</p><p><strong>#Your Rights</strong></p><p><strong>Access:</strong> You can request access to the personal information we hold about you.</p><p><strong>Correction:</strong> You can request that we correct any inaccuracies in your personal information.</p><p><strong>Deletion:</strong> You can request that we delete your personal information, subject to certain exceptions.</p><p><strong>Changes to This Policy</strong> We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any significant changes by posting the new policy on our website.</p><p><strong>Contact Us</strong> If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at contact@email.com</p>'),
